%BOM---------------------
Date:12/1/2011 12:53:14 AM
From:Spekulatius
re HPQ, I was surprised by the weak number in the printing business. Printing
has been one of HPQ cash cow but my thinking is that the printing business may
have just started to go into a secular decline.

A few days ago, I looked at former German Blue chips and was surprised about
the trouble that the large area commercial printing machine companies like
Heidelberger Druck and Man Roland are in. All of these companies were highly
profitable 10 years ago and then started a secular decline about 7-8 years ago
that keeps on getting worse and worse. This is probably not a surprise since
many commercial printers are hurting, newspapers are hurting and print ads
slowly but surely get replaced by the web.

Now, I think it is the PC printers turn, since it is easy to shown show
pictures on the TV, store tons of them on a thumb drive or just show the
pictures on a tablet. Really there is less and less reason to put pictures on
paper (if it were not for my computer illiterate parents I would not need a
color printer at all). I think this business is going the way of the typewriter
and this is bad news for HPQ, since that is one of the few sectors where they
have a moat.
%EOM----------------------

