Date:12/3/2011 4:26:08 PM
From:robert b furman
Hi CB,

I always think of buying a stock as a right to the future cash flow of the
business.

When markets collapse or decline, everybody loses equity (unless of course they
are short).

If I own a stock in a company - I'm always sure they will survive and make a
product that will have future demand.

Implosion / collapses are just a time where I should 've had fresh cash or
buying power to take advantage of the discount.

It always happens.

Bob
